The course consists of a short introduction and six topics: 1) the quality of the teaching material; 2) the structure and language of the texts; 3) illustrations in the texts; 4) tasks to assess text comprehension; 
5) the formation of values in the textbook; 6) basic rules for the use of other authors' work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Acquiring the theoretical bases for the composing of textbooks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After acquiring the content of the course, - the student knows the foundations of composing textbooks, - the student is able to create the structure of study material, - the student knows the possibilities for interesting and comprehensible presentation of study material, - the student is able to use illustrations in the study material, - the student recognises value forming elements in the study material, - the student knows the main principles of using the works of other authors.
